# Notion Widgets — Project Rules

## Architecture
- Single HTML files per widget, all sharing core.js as a library
- core.js: SyncEngine (Cloudflare KV sync), theme engine, dragon game, shared utilities
- Cloudflare Worker: https://widget-sync.lordgrape-widgets.workers.dev
- Auth: passphrase stored in localStorage as _sync_passphrase, sent as X-Widget-Key header
- All widgets run inside Notion iframe embeds (typical height 180px, varies)
- Expand mode: Press F toggles .container to fill the iframe viewport via CSS (position:fixed + 100vw/vh). Sandbox-safe, no Fullscreen API. Lives in core.js. All widgets inherit. Esc also collapses.
- Weather click: Copies forecast URL to clipboard (window.open blocked in Notion's sandboxed iframes).

## Widgets
- horizon.html: Main dashboard widget — clock, timetable, dragon pet game, milestones
- clock.html: Standalone clock widget
- timetable.html: Schedule widget (multi-day blocks, week + today views)
- quotes.html: Daily quotes widget

## Milestone system (horizon.html)
- No hardcoded milestones. All user-created via Add Milestone form (+ on radar panel).
- Stored in localStorage (`horizon_milestones`) and SyncEngine (`dragon.milestones` JSON string).
- Archive: `horizon_milestones_archive` + `dragon.milestones_archive`; past dates auto-archive with XP (once per id, `dragon_milestone_claimed`).
- Completed milestones listed under Stats (info button) → Completed Milestones.
- Categories: academic, military, career, personal, law, fitness (colours + icons in `DEFAULT_CATEGORIES`).
- Single-click event row: detail popup. Double-click: edit. Delete in edit form.
- `processExpiredMilestones()` runs on load, on SyncEngine ready, and on tab visibility resume.

## Achievements (horizon.html — 36 total)
- Original 22 + 14 new (milestone, weather, streak, completionist, weekend, bars, speed evolve).
- Stored in localStorage `dragon_ach` as `{ id: timestamp }`.
- `checkAch()` runs every 10s, on XP gain paths, and after milestone changes.
- `all_ach` (Completionist) unlocks when every other achievement is unlocked first.

## Dragon Game (horizon.html)
- 6 stages: Egg (0 XP) → Hatchling (1000) → Whelp (5000) → Drake (20000) → Dragon (60000) → Elder (120000)
- Stage 0 (Egg): Rendered via Three.js (EggScene module) with Canvas 2D fallback
- Stages 1+: Canvas 2D rendering (drawDragon function)

### Weather system (horizon.html + clock.html)
- Open-Meteo current conditions (same `current=` field set). 30min TTL.
- Single shared payload: localStorage `_weather_cache` and SyncEngine `user.weather` (`{ ts, data }` JSON string). Read SyncEngine first, then localStorage; writes update both.
- `weatherData` / shared `data`: `{ temp, code, condition, icon, type, humidity, wind }`
- `getWeatherType(code)` returns: `clear` | `cloudy` | `rain` | `snow` | `fog` | `storm`
- Horizon: `fetchWeather()` lat/lon from `user.lat`/`user.lon` (fallback Toronto). Weather badge positioned above XP bar (`bottom: 28px`).
- Clock: same cache + same API when refreshing; `SyncEngine.onReady` re-runs `fetchWeather()` after pull. Forecast overlay still uses `WLAT`/`WLON` (unchanged).

### Ambient systems (horizon egg — zero-interaction, scale with `getStage()`)
- `returnGlow`: set in `initDS()` when previous `lastVisit` was 2h+ before refresh; fades via decay in the active renderer (`drawEgg` or `EggScene.render`)
- Time-of-day particles (Canvas egg): morning = gold dust, evening = fireflies, night = blue sparkles
- Weather particles (Canvas egg): rain streaks, snowflakes, sun rays, fog wisps, storm flash
- Proximity warmth: heat particles rising when pointer is near the egg
- Seasonal nest accents: spring buds, summer gold, autumn amber, winter frost (sleep activity)
- Three.js crack glow: independent breathing rhythm per crack (desync from egg heartbeat)
- Particle counts use `base + getStage(DS.xp) * multiplier`; intensities use `base + stage * scale`
- Future stages (1–5) extend in their draw functions with stage-specific responses
- XP stored in SyncEngine under 'dragon' namespace
- Bars: rations, morale, readiness (0-100, decay over time)
- Activity system: ACT_POOL per stage, day-phase dependent

## SyncEngine (core.js)
- v3 architecture: localStorage primary, Cloudflare KV remote sync
- Namespace-based: each widget feature gets a namespace key (e.g. 'dragon', 'clock')
- Merge strategies:
  - MONOTONIC_KEYS (xp, streak): Math.max() — highest value always wins
  - UNION_KEYS (achievements): JSON array set union
  - Default: newest timestamp wins (_ts field comparison)
- Daily XP cap: 1200/day enforced in addDragonXP()
- Monotonic enforcement: XP can never decrease client-side

## Worker (Cloudflare)
- XP validation on PUT for dragon namespace:
  - XP can never decrease (patches to old value if attempted)
  - Per-push delta capped at 2000 XP
  - Non-destructive: patches only XP, lets other state through
- Also serves Notion API proxy for milestones (GET /notion/milestones)

## Frameworks & Libraries
- Three.js r160 (CDN) — used ONLY for egg rendering in horizon.html
- GSAP (CDN) — used for animations across widgets
- No other frameworks. Vanilla JS everywhere else.

## Style & Conventions
- var (not let/const) in widget HTML files for consistency with existing code
- let/const in core.js SyncEngine IIFE (modern style within the module)
- Canadian English in all user-facing strings
- Dark/light theme support required — use Core.isDark and Core.on('theme-change', ...)
- All colours must have both dark and light variants

## Key Constants
- DAILY_VIS_CAP = 200, DAILY_LOGIN_XP = 40, INTERACT_XP = 8, INTERACT_CAP = 5
- STREAK_BASE = 20, STREAK_CAP = 150
- Dragon canvas: id="dc", size DSZ (180), DPR-scaled

## Testing
- Open HTML files directly in browser or via GitHub Pages
- F12 console: look for [Horizon], [Core], [SyncEngine] prefixed logs
- Test both dark and light themes
- Test with WebGL disabled (egg should fall back to Canvas 2D)
- Test cross-device sync by opening on two devices and earning XP on one

## Spec Pages
- Full architecture specs are maintained in Notion by the user's AI assistant
- The human will paste relevant spec content into prompts when needed
- Always ask for the relevant spec section if making changes to unfamiliar code

# Design Token System (core.js v4)
- All colours use CSS custom properties: --surface-0/1/2/3, --text-primary/secondary/tertiary, --accent-primary/secondary, --border-subtle/default/accent
- All radii use --radius-sm/md/lg/xl
- All transitions use --transition-fast/default/slow/spring
- All shadows use --shadow-sm/md/lg/glow
- Shared glass utility classes: .glass-card, .glass-button, .glass-pill, .glass-input
- Never hardcode colours, radii, transitions, or shadows

# Accessibility
- Core.a11y.announce(text) for screen reader announcements
- Core.a11y.trap(container) for modal focus trapping
- Core.a11y.roving(container, selector) for arrow-key group navigation
- Core.tooltip.attach(el, text) for hover/focus tooltips
- Core.ripple(el, colour?) for interaction feedback
- All tabs use role="tablist"/role="tab"/role="tabpanel" pattern
- All interactive elements have aria-labels and focus-visible outlines

# Fonts
- Inter: UI text (loaded via Google Fonts)
- JetBrains Mono: Monospace numbers — clocks, timers, counters, XP

# quotes.html v3 — copy button removed, widget is now fully passive (no interactive elements except 3D drag spin)

# Quotes spin sound v3 (quotes.html)
- 3D drag spin plays a velocity-reactive Cmaj7 chord pad (C3, E4, G4, B4) via Web Audio oscillators
- Each voice has a velocity threshold: root enters first, upper voices layer in at higher speeds
- Subtle per-voice vibrato (3.5–5 Hz LFO, ±0.3% pitch) adds organic shimmer
- No noise source — pure tones only, can never sound harsh
- Quadratic gain curves, 80ms ramp (updateSpin), 200ms decay (silenceSpin)
- initSpin() lazy-inits on first drag via getAudioCtx()

# Timer persistence (clock.html)
- Timer state (running/paused) is persisted to SyncEngine `clock.timer_state` so it survives Notion iframe reload
- saveTimerState() writes on start/pause/visibilitychange/beforeunload; restoreTimerState() resumes on load
- SyncEngine.remove('clock', 'timer_state') on reset and completion
- Timer presets: 25m, 50m, 90m + Custom input (evidence-based learning blocks)

# Timer preset hints: PRESETS array includes ttTitle/ttText for inline hover hints.
# #presetHint element sits between .presets and .ring-wrap, expands on hover.
# showPresetHint()/hidePresetHint() handle height expand + typewriter text reveal.
# Typewriter: 18ms/char, once per preset per session (_phTyped tracker), instant on revisit.
# Hover intent: 300ms delay before hint opens. Passing through chips does not trigger.
# CUSTOM_TOOLTIP holds hint data for the Custom chip.

# Presence tracking: gaps under 10 min (_PRES_AWAY_THRESHOLD) count as active Notion time.
# Only gaps >10 min are subtracted. Accounts for Notion app iframe unloading on page navigation.

- Dark-mode background orbs: Core.orbAlpha 0.025 (light 0.02).
- Tilt glow overlay removed. initTilt provides 3D perspective tilt only, no radial-gradient spotlight.

# Schedule Widget v3 (timetable.html)
- Data model: blocks with nested `days` array: [{ day: 0-6, start: "HH:MM", end: "HH:MM" }]
- SyncEngine key is still 'courses' under 'timetable' namespace (backward compat)
- Fields: name, description (was prof), location (was room), color, days[]
- v2 flat format auto-migrates on boot via getBlocks()
- Milestones removed from timetable embed — will be re-added later
- "Block" = universal schedule item (class, shift, parade, gym, etc.)
- Settings list: pencil (✎) opens add form in edit mode (pre-filled). `editBlock(id, data)` updates the block in SyncEngine; `showAddForm(existingBlock?)` covers add vs Save.

# Horizon milestone system (v2)
- Milestones use 3 tiers (small/medium/large) with SCALED XP based on current evolution gap
- scaledMilestoneXP(catId) returns pct * (nextStageXP - currentStageXP)
- Old 6-category IDs auto-migrate to 'medium' via migrateCategoryId()
- No user-defined XP field — tier determines reward
- Evolution titles: Dormant → Spark → Ember → Blaze → Sovereign → Mythic (no military ranks)
- visibilitychange re-pulls SyncEngine state for cross-device XP sync
